     * [https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/saltstack-infrast
       ructure-creating-salt-states-for-haproxy-load-balancers]SaltStack
       Infrastructure: Creating Salt States for HAProxy Load Balancers -
       Part 5 of 6 in the series Managing Development Environments with
       SaltStack.
     * [https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/saltstack-infrast
       ructure-creating-salt-states-for-mysql-database-servers]SaltStack
       Infrastructure: Creating Salt States for MySQL Database Servers -
       Part 6 in the series Managing Development Environments with
       SaltStack.
     * [https://www.linuxjournal.com/content/getting-started-salt-stack-ot
       her-configuration-management-system-built-python]Getting Started
       with SaltStack - the Other Configuration Management System Built
       with Python - A Linux Journal "Getting started" from 2013.
     * [http://www.aaronbell.com/lets-make-salt-minions-on-digitalocean/]C
       reate an army of Salt minions on DigitalOcean - Combine the
       simplicity of Salt with DigitalOcean's snapshot and image feature.
     * [http://hittaruki.info/post/vagrant-saltstack-tutorial/]Vagrant &
       SaltStack Quickstart Tutorial - Getting started with SaltStack and
       Vagrant.
     * [https://thereluctanttecchie.blogspot.com/2014/01/salt-api-crash-co
       urse.html]Salt-API, A Crash Course - Get a barebones salt-api proof
       of concept up and running.
     * [http://blog.infracloud.io/saltstack-tutorial-part-1/]Getting
       Started with SaltStack - Part 1 - Simple setup and play around on
       the command line.
     * [http://blog.infracloud.io/saltstack-tutorial-part-2/]Getting
       Started with SaltStack - Part 2 - Write a complete module for
       installing and configure a web server.
     * [https://www.unixmen.com/saltstack-examples/]SaltStack Examples -
       Will teach you some of default functions in a quick way.
     * [https://honza.ca/2013/12/masterless-saltstack]Masterless Saltstack
       - A simple guide on how to use SaltStack in masterless mode.
     * [https://blog.badgerops.net/2017/04/10/getting-started-with-salt-wo
       rkspace/]Getting Started with Saltstack and salt-workspace -
       Learning SaltStack by setting up a salt-workspace.
     * [https://blog.badgerops.net/2017/04/22/getting-started-with-salt-st
       ructure-2/]Getting started with Salt Structure - Learn how to setup
       a structured SaltStack workspace.
     * [https://blog.badgerops.net/2017/05/23/writing-a-custom-salt-grain/
       ]Writing a custom Salt Grain - Writing a custom Salt Grain, and why
       you might want to.
     * [http://bencane.com/2014/12/30/building-self-healing-applications-w
       ith-salt-api/]Building Self-Healing Applications - Automate the
       detection and first action to correct errors in your
       infrastructure.
     * [https://github.com/redmage123/Introduction-to-Saltstack]Introducti
       on to SaltStack - A two day course designed to quickly introduce
       System Administrators and Application Developers on how to start
       using Saltstack.
     * [https://medium.com/@timlwhite/the-simplest-way-to-learn-saltstack-
       cd9f5edbc967]The Simplest Way to Learn SaltStack - Start to learn
       the basics of SaltStack by setting it up in Docker.
     * [https://www.tutorialspoint.com/saltstack/saltstack_quick_guide.htm
       ]SaltStack - Quick Guide - Part of the larger "Learn
       SaltStack"-tutorial at Tutorials Point.

Code

     * [https://github.com/zulily/alkali]zulily/alkali - A collections of
       SaltStack states and pillar data that provide just the basics for
       provisioning Linux instances that may be built upon.
     * [https://github.com/zulily/buoyant]zulily/buoyant - Leverages
       docker to provide an alternative to VM-centric SaltStack
       development environments.
     * [https://k8s-salt.opsnotice.xyz/]valentin2105/Kubernetes-Saltstack
       - Saltstack recipe to deploy Kubernetes cluster from scratch.
     * [https://github.com/madflojo/masterless-salt-base]madflojo/masterle
       ss-salt-base - Quickly bootstrap a generic(ish) Ubuntu server. One
       that is ready to host Docker containers.

Books

     * [http://shop.oreilly.com/product/0636920033240.do]O'Reilly - Salt
