Blogposts and opinions

     * [http://www.salttofinish.com/]Salt To Finish - "the original
       SaltStack blog".
     * [https://opsnotice.xyz/docker-with-saltstack/]Docker with SaltStack
       - How-to use SaltStack on a virtual cloud server based on Debian or
       Ubuntu.
     * [https://blog.ryandlane.com/2014/08/04/moving-away-from-puppet-salt
       stack-or-ansible/]Moving away from Puppet: SaltStack or Ansible? -
       Salt and Ansible as viable and excellent options for replacing
       Puppet.
     * [https://stevebennett.me/2014/02/17/one-week-of-salt-frustrations-a
       nd-reflections/]One week of Salt: frustrations and reflections -
       First hand experiences from a Chef user.
     * [http://bencane.com/2013/09/03/getting-started-with-saltstack-by-ex
       ample-automatically-installing-nginx/]Getting started with
       SaltStack by example: Automatically Installing nginx - A good
       getting started guide for both Salt master and minions.
     * [https://makina-corpus.com/blog/metier/2014/saltstack-manage-entrie
       s-in-unmanaged-files-with-file-blockreplace]SaltStack: Manage
       entries in unmanaged files with File Blockreplace - How to use the
       SaltStack's core file.blockreplace.
     * [http://btmiller.com/2016/11/27/docker-swarm-1.12-cluster-orchestra
       tion-with-saltstack.html]Docker Swarm 1.12 Cluster Orchestration
       with SaltStack - Let's see how we can automate the spin-up of a
       cluster using SaltStack.
     * [https://www.amon.cx/blog/saltstack-review/]SaltStack - Review and
       how it fares against Ansible and Puppet - As seen from the Salt
       perspective.
     * [http://fabianlee.org/2016/10/18/saltstack-keeping-salt-pillar-data
       -encrypted-using-gpg/]SaltStack: Keeping Salt Pillar data encrypted
       using GPG - On secure encryption/decryption of pillar data.
     * [https://gijs.io/2017/02/28/secure-pillar-data-in-saltstack-with-gp
       g/]Secure Pillar in SaltStack with GPG - Encrypting your pillar
       data can be done with GPG.
     * [http://blog.simonmetzger.de/2018/02/salt-napalm-k8s-network-automa
       tion/]Network-Automation with Salt, NAPALM and Kubernetes - How to
       manage legacy devices that are not able to install software
       natively on themselves.
     * [https://mirceaulinic.net/2017-12-19-salt-pure-python/]Python
       development for infrastructure management using Salt - The
       overlooked side of Salt and some best practices.
     * [https://duncan.codes/2016/05/18/using-salt-like-ansible.html]Using
       Salt like Ansible - How to use Salt in a way similar to Ansible.

